Wilmar International expects a gradual improvement in its China operations  a positive sign as the country contributed 51% of its revenue in 2022  says Nomura analyst Raghavendra Diveka in a research report. However  the agribusiness company's palm-oil refining margins could remain weak in 2Q due to weak oleochemical and biodiesel demand  he cautions. Commodity prices  including that of vegetable oils have also come off last year's highs  although sugar could be a bright spot  with prices expected to remain strong amid ongoing shortages  the analyst adds. Nomura maintains a buy rating and target price of S$5.00 on the stock  which is 1.5% lower at S$3.87.
